  "prompt": "Where can I get very traditional plastering service in Boston?",
  "response": "If you're looking for very traditional plastering services in Boston, here are some recommendations to help you find skilled artisans and companies specializing in traditional techniques:\n\n### 1. **Plaster Artisans or Restoration Companies**\n   - **John Canning & Co.**: Based in Connecticut but serves the Boston area, this company specializes in historic plaster restoration and traditional plastering techniques. They are highly respected for their work on historic buildings.\n   - **EverGreene Architectural Arts**: While based in New York, they work nationwide and have expertise in traditional plastering and decorative finishes for historic properties.\n   - **Boston Plastering**: A local company that focuses on traditional plastering and restoration work. They have experience with historic homes and buildings in the Boston area.\n\n### 2. **Historic Preservation Networks**\n   - **Preservation Massachusetts**: This organization can provide recommendations for contractors and artisans who specialize in traditional plastering and historic restoration.\n   - **Boston Preservation Alliance**: They maintain a list of contractors and craftsmen experienced in traditional building techniques, including plastering.\n\n### 3. **Local Craftsmen and Union Tradespeople**\n   - **Plasterers' and Cement Masons' Local 534**: Union plasterers often have training in traditional techniques. Contacting the local union can help you find skilled professionals.\n   - **Independent Artisans**: Look for independent plasterers who specialize in historic restoration. Word of mouth or local historical societies can be a good resource.\n\n### 4. **Architects and Contractors Specializing in Historic Homes**\n   - **Architectural firms or contractors** that focus on historic properties often work with traditional plasterers. Examples include **Albert, Righter & Tittmann Architects** or **Jablonski Building Conservation, Inc.**\n\n### 5. **Ask Local Historical Societies**\n   - **The Boston Athenaeum** or **The Society for the Preservation of New England Antiquities (Historic New England)** may have recommendations for traditional plasterers.\n\n### Tips for Finding the Right Service:\n- **Check Reviews and Portfolios**: Review past projects to ensure they align with your needs.\n- **Request Samples**: A skilled traditional plasterer should be able to demonstrate their work or provide samples.\n- **Visit Historic Homes**: If you\u2019re working on a historic property, consult with owners of similar homes for recommendations.\n\nBy reaching out to these resources, you\u2019ll likely find a professional who can provide the traditional plastering service you\u2019re looking for in the Boston area.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
